				<section id="MobileClinic">
					<div class="">
						<h4>The Mobile Nutrition Clinic</h4>
						<p>Goshen’s Fountain of Nutrition and Health is operating a Mobile Nutrition Clinic to address Nutrition issues among the children, pregnant and lactating mothers and PLWHIV/AIDS undergoing Anti-Retroviral Treatment. We are currently running the Nutrition clinic in Goma Health Center 3 in Mukono – Uganda and the surrounding villages. We shall be rolling out the clinic services to the rest of the country.</p>
						<ul>
							<h5>The clinic activities include;</h5>
							<li>Screening children for malnutrition by taking their MUAC, Height, length (Babies) and weight where the acutely malnourished are referred to government Nutrition centers (Mwanamugimu) and other better equipped facilities. Other cases are managed by giving supplements to the affected. We undertake a feeding program for the malnourished children on a specially developed supplement by the Goshen’s team by giving rations to the care givers with clear preparation guidelines. The care givers are trained on making local recipes of nutritious mixtures using the staple foods available.</li>
							<li>We have a follow up program on the currently managed cases of malnourished children to assess progress on the client.</li>
							<li>As Goshen’s, we conduct awareness sessions for the care givers on the preparation of nutritious meals for the vulnerable groups.</li>
							<li>We give pre and post testing counseling services to the care givers of the children in relation to HIV. We encouraged mothers who bring children for nutrition assessments to voluntarily have the HIV status of their children and their own ascertained by running serology tests. The counseling services are offered by a team of qualified Goshen’s counselors. We also encourage the mothers to come along with their husbands for HIV pretest counseling for eventual voluntary testing. We encourage couples to come for counseling and testing.</li>
							<li>As Goshen’s, we encourage households to have HIV status of their entire households established.</li>
							<li>In conjunction with the ART (Anti-Retroviral Treatment) clinic at the health centers, the clients undertaking ARV therapy are advised on the appropriate meal composition to take care of the side effects of the drugs and also boost the immunity system to fight the opportunistic infections. Nutrition is a crucial component in the ARV administration that cannot be under estimated and the clients are enlightened on the linkages between HIV and nutrition.</li>
							<li>As Goshen’s, we offer follow up counseling services to the HIV positive clients to hear their views and find out how they are coping with the drugs. For clients that are not following their drug administration schedules, the counseling team establishes the reason for failure to adherence.</li>
							<li>We undertake follow up on clients who are on Anti-Retroviral Treatment (ART) to ensure compliance on drug taking and also as reminders to keep appointment of clinic visits to pick drugs. This is undertaken through bulk SMSs we periodically send to the clients. The clients are also given nutritional counseling.</li>
							<li>As Goshen’s we carry on awareness programs in communities, public and private institutions on the dangers of HIV/AIDS and passing on the slogan "SAYING NO TO HIV STARTS WITH ME". </li>
							<li>As Goshen’s, we promote safe male circumcision program for the children, the youth and the adults as a strategy to reduces the infection rates for HIV and other sexually transmitted diseases like Gonorrhea, and syphilis. We design and pass on messages in local languages about the spread and dangers of HIV & other STDs.</li>
							<li>Other than services on HIV and Nutrition, Goshen’s Fountain of Nutrition and Health also carries on screening clients for others medical sicknesses like High blood pressure and skin problems. Other conditions likes Diabetes, dental, optical issues will be addressed once Goshen’s gets the capacity in terms of facilities and equipment to manage.</li>
							<li>As Goshen’s we move clinical services near the needing population for those who cannot afford transport to the health centers.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
